      {
        "id": 272925,
        "name": null,
        "username": "Kobold",
        "avatar_template": "/user_avatar/forum.magicball.net/kobold/{size}/393_2.png",
        "created_at": "2006-12-17T11:47:55.000Z",
        "cooked": "<p>Hi. <img src=\"//forum.magicball.net/plugins/discourse-lba-emoji/images/takam/slight_smile.png?v=12\" title=\":slight_smile:\" class=\"emoji emoji-custom\" alt=\":slight_smile:\" loading=\"lazy\" width=\"20\" height=\"20\"></p>\n<p>First of all, get <a href=\"http://moonbase.szwol6.net/index.php?page=d_prog\" rel=\"noopener nofollow ugc\">LBA Package Editor</a>. It allows you to edit HQR files from the original LBA games.<br>\nGo into your LBA 1/2 folder and create a backup of Body.HQR. Then open the original with the Package Editor. You get a list of characters. Choose the character you want to play with and click Extract selected entries. Save the file somewhere.<br>\nThen go to the first few entries all belonging to Twinsen, select them all, and click Replace selected entries with and load the file you saved before.<br>\nNext to output file, click on the green arrow. Then say build output file.</p>\n<p>Play the game.<br>\nWhen youre finished having fun, get your backup of body.HQR back to your LBA folder. <img src=\"//forum.magicball.net/plugins/discourse-lba-emoji/images/takam/wink.png?v=12\" title=\":wink:\" class=\"emoji emoji-custom\" alt=\":wink:\" loading=\"lazy\" width=\"20\" height=\"20\"></p>\n<p>And feel free to ask if theres something you dont understand.</p>",
