      {
        "id": 273020,
        "name": null,
        "username": "xesf",
        "avatar_template": "/user_avatar/forum.magicball.net/xesf/{size}/122_2.png",
        "created_at": "2006-12-18T11:59:46.000Z",
        "cooked": "<aside class=\"quote no-group\" data-username=\"Kobold\" data-post=\"2\" data-topic=\"10495\">\n<div class=\"title\">\n<div class=\"quote-controls\"></div>\n<img loading=\"lazy\" alt=\"\" width=\"24\" height=\"24\" src=\"//forum.magicball.net/user_avatar/localhost/kobold/48/393_2.png\" class=\"avatar\"> Kobold:</div>\n<blockquote>\n<p>Hi. <img src=\"//forum.magicball.net/plugins/discourse-lba-emoji/images/takam/slight_smile.png?v=12\" title=\":slight_smile:\" class=\"emoji emoji-custom\" alt=\":slight_smile:\" loading=\"lazy\" width=\"20\" height=\"20\"></p>\n<p>First of all, get <a href=\"http://moonbase.szwol6.net/index.php?page=d_prog\" rel=\"noopener nofollow ugc\">LBA Package Editor</a>. It allows you to edit HQR files from the original LBA games.<br>\nGo into your LBA 1/2 folder and create a backup of Body.HQR. Then open the original with the Package Editor. You get a list of characters. Choose the character you want to play with and click Extract selected entries. Save the file somewhere.<br>\nThen go to the first few entries all belonging to Twinsen, select them all, and click Replace selected entries with and load the file you saved before.<br>\nNext to output file, click on the green arrow. Then say build output file.</p>\n<p>Play the game.<br>\nWhen youre finished having fun, get your backup of body.HQR back to your LBA folder. <img src=\"//forum.magicball.net/plugins/discourse-lba-emoji/images/takam/wink.png?v=12\" title=\":wink:\" class=\"emoji emoji-custom\" alt=\":wink:\" loading=\"lazy\" width=\"20\" height=\"20\"></p>\n<p>And feel free to ask if theres something you dont understand.</p>\n</blockquote>\n</aside>\n<p>If you only want to change to another character without editing him, you dont need to save it. Only drag the body entry you want to replace in the place you want or press F2 in the entry you want to edit and write &gt; entry number of the deserved character.</p>",
